<task id="SPE-020" project="SDAP SPE Admin App">
  <metadata>
    <title>File Versions/Thumbnails/Sharing Endpoints</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>2h</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, api, graph, phase-1</tags>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <dependencies>SPE-017</dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Implement file metadata endpoints for version history, thumbnails, and sharing links. These provide administrators with deeper insight into file state and the ability to generate sharing links for collaboration.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer familiar with Minimal APIs and Microsoft Graph</role>
  <goal>Three working endpoints: list file versions, get thumbnails, and create sharing links via Graph API.</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Use Minimal API endpoint pattern — no controllers, no Azure Functions.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Use endpoint filters for authorization — no global auth middleware.</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/graph-sdk-v5.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <context>
    <background>Version history lets administrators see the evolution of a file and restore previous versions if needed. Thumbnails enable visual previews in the admin UI file browser. Sharing links allow administrators to generate temporary or persistent links for users who need access to specific files.</background>
  </context>
  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Implement versions endpoint">Add GET /api/spe/containers/{id}/items/{itemId}/versions?configId={id} that returns version history from Graph API.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Implement thumbnails endpoint">Add GET /api/spe/containers/{id}/items/{itemId}/thumbnails?configId={id} that returns thumbnail URLs from Graph API.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Implement sharing endpoint">Add POST /api/spe/containers/{id}/items/{itemId}/share?configId={id} that creates a sharing link via Graph API, accepting link type and scope.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Test endpoints">Verify version list returns chronological versions, thumbnails return valid URLs, and sharing creates accessible links.</step>
  </steps>
  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Endpoints/SpeAdmin/ContainerItemEndpoints.cs</output>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">GET versions returns a list of file versions with version ID, modified date, and modified by.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">GET thumbnails returns thumbnail URLs for the specified file.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">POST share creates a sharing link and returns the link URL.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Endpoints return appropriate errors for non-existent items.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
